article.headline: San Jose St. 78, UC Irvine 68
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Adrian Oliver scored 29 points and had seven rebounds, leading San Jose State to a 78-68 victory over UC Irvine on Monday night. Mac Peterson added 13 points for the Spartans (7-5), while C.J. Webster and Justin Graham had 10 points apiece. Eric Wise led Irvine (6-6) with a career-high 31 points. Senior guard Michael Hunter added 19 to become the 19th player in school history to score at least 1,000 points in his career. He entered the game with 999. San Jose State opened the second half with an 8-1 run to build a 49-36 lead and pushed its advantage to 59-44 on Robert Owens' 3-pointer with 12:47 to play. The Anteaters later put together a 7-0 run to pull within 61-53, but they never got any closer. Spartans center Chris Oakes was reinstated by the NCAA on Monday after missing the past three due to an eligibility issue.
